    "For h -1 g [ x ′] is the set of proper filters X in A such that h g (X) = h -1 [X] ∈ x ′, which means x ′ ∈ h -1 [X], which means h(x ′) ∈ X, and h(x ′) is the set of proper filters X in A such that h(x ′) ∈ X.For part 2, we must show that if h is surjective, then (i)h g (Y) ⊑ ′ h g (X) implies Y ⊑ X (so h g is injective), (ii) h g (X)R ′ i h g (Y)implies XR i Y, and (iii) for every x ∈ P g there is ax ′ ∈ P ′ g such that h g [ x] = h g [S] ∩ x ′.",
